  <refnamediv>
    <refname>RPI_mcp23s17Setup</refname>
    <refpurpose>Function for setting up 16-bit MCP23s17 SPI GPIO expansion chip.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   RPI_mcp23s17Setup(pinBase,spiPort,devId)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>pinBase:</term>
      <listitem><para> any number above 64. The consecutive 16 pins will be allocated alongwith.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>spiPort:</term>
      <listitem><para> 0 or 1 for one of the two SPI ports on the Raspberry Pi.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>devId  :</term>
      <listitem><para> the ID of the MCP23s17 on the SPI port.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
This function setups the extension module for the 16-bit MCP23s17 SPI GPIO expansion chip.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
